Crossbench peers in the House of Lords are preparing an attack on the Government's controversial plans to rewrite the Northern Ireland Protocol when parliament returns from its summer break next week. Two aspects of the bill are reportedly causing concern in the Lords, including the UK’s plan to use the legislation to switch off parts of the protocol — which some believe breaches international law — and the significant powers ministers would gain under the new provisions. Peers are expected to be orchestrating their plot to dismantle Ms Truss's master plan in a meeting next week behind closed doors. Peter Ricketts, a crossbench peer and the former head of the UK’s Foreign, Commonwealth and Development Office, said: “There will be weeks and weeks and weeks of battle over this bill, because there’s a lot in it that many lords on all sides will really hate.” FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...